<span id="freeTextContainer6746180851194245499">I thought I was enlightened and knew everything. I thought I had read every masterpiece ever written, and then Luís C. came and recommended this book to me and I went back to my actual size and confessed with shame that I had never read Mark Twain&apos;s writing.<br/><br/>So I quickly went to Google and checked who was the writer and then I read this book. Immediately I was fascinated - less than the story itself and more than the writing and the great ideas behind it considering the date of writing itself.<br/><br/>Tha</span>
  <span id="freeText6746180851194245499" style="display:none">I thought I was enlightened and knew everything. I thought I had read every masterpiece ever written, and then Luís C. came and recommended this book to me and I went back to my actual size and confessed with shame that I had never read Mark Twain's writing.<br /><br />So I quickly went to Google and checked who was the writer and then I read this book. Immediately I was fascinated - less than the story itself and more than the writing and the great ideas behind it considering the date of writing itself.<br /><br />Thank you Luís C. for the introduction with Twain's book.</span>
